@page "/Accordion"
@rendermode InteractiveWebAssembly

<h1>Accordion Demo</h1>

<h2>Single Mode (Default)</h2>
<AccordionRoot DefaultValue="item-1">
    <AccordionItem Value="item-1">
        <AccordionHeader>
            <AccordionTrigger class="btn btn-primary">What is ArkUI?</AccordionTrigger>
        </AccordionHeader>
        <AccordionContent>
            <p>ArkUI is a Blazor component library focused on WCAG-compliant, fully customizable headless components.</p>
        </AccordionContent>
    </AccordionItem>

    <AccordionItem Value="item-2">
        <AccordionHeader>
            <AccordionTrigger class="btn btn-primary">Is it accessible?</AccordionTrigger>
        </AccordionHeader>
        <AccordionContent>
            <p>Yes! All components are built with WCAG accessibility compliance, including proper ARIA attributes and keyboard navigation.</p>
        </AccordionContent>
    </AccordionItem>

    <AccordionItem Value="item-3">
        <AccordionHeader>
            <AccordionTrigger class="btn btn-primary">Can I style it?</AccordionTrigger>
        </AccordionHeader>
        <AccordionContent>
            <p>Absolutely. ArkUI components are headless, meaning they provide functionality without opinionated styling. Use data attributes like <code>data-state="open"</code> for styling hooks.</p>
        </AccordionContent>
    </AccordionItem>
</AccordionRoot>

<h2>Multiple Mode</h2>
<AccordionRoot Type="AccordionType.Multiple" DefaultValues="@(["feature-1", "feature-2"])">
    <AccordionItem Value="feature-1">
        <AccordionHeader>
            <AccordionTrigger>Feature 1: Headless Design</AccordionTrigger>
        </AccordionHeader>
        <AccordionContent>
            <p>Components provide structure and behavior without opinionated styling.</p>
        </AccordionContent>
    </AccordionItem>

    <AccordionItem Value="feature-2">
        <AccordionHeader>
            <AccordionTrigger>Feature 2: Full Accessibility</AccordionTrigger>
        </AccordionHeader>
        <AccordionContent>
            <p>Built-in ARIA attributes, keyboard navigation, and screen reader support.</p>
        </AccordionContent>
    </AccordionItem>

    <AccordionItem Value="feature-3">
        <AccordionHeader>
            <AccordionTrigger>Feature 3: Cross-Render Mode</AccordionTrigger>
        </AccordionHeader>
        <AccordionContent>
            <p>Works across WASM, SSR, and Interactive Server Blazor render modes.</p>
        </AccordionContent>
    </AccordionItem>
</AccordionRoot>

<h2>Non-Collapsible Single Mode</h2>
<AccordionRoot DefaultValue="always-1" Collapsible="false">
    <AccordionItem Value="always-1">
        <AccordionHeader>
            <AccordionTrigger>Always One Open</AccordionTrigger>
        </AccordionHeader>
        <AccordionContent>
            <p>In non-collapsible mode, at least one item must always be open.</p>
        </AccordionContent>
    </AccordionItem>

    <AccordionItem Value="always-2">
        <AccordionHeader>
            <AccordionTrigger>Try Closing Me</AccordionTrigger>
        </AccordionHeader>
        <AccordionContent>
            <p>You can switch to this item, but you can't close the last open item.</p>
        </AccordionContent>
    </AccordionItem>
</AccordionRoot>

<h2>With Disabled Items</h2>
<AccordionRoot DefaultValue="enabled-1">
    <AccordionItem Value="enabled-1">
        <AccordionHeader>
            <AccordionTrigger>Enabled Item</AccordionTrigger>
        </AccordionHeader>
        <AccordionContent>
            <p>This item works normally.</p>
        </AccordionContent>
    </AccordionItem>

    <AccordionItem Value="disabled-1" Disabled="true">
        <AccordionHeader>
            <AccordionTrigger>Disabled Item</AccordionTrigger>
        </AccordionHeader>
        <AccordionContent>
            <p>You shouldn't be able to see this!</p>
        </AccordionContent>
    </AccordionItem>

    <AccordionItem Value="enabled-2">
        <AccordionHeader>
            <AccordionTrigger>Another Enabled Item</AccordionTrigger>
        </AccordionHeader>
        <AccordionContent>
            <p>Keyboard navigation skips the disabled item.</p>
        </AccordionContent>
    </AccordionItem>
</AccordionRoot>
